<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Edouard Mendy is on the brink of becoming a Chelsea player and the deal could be even be confirmed by Thursday night, according to his agent.</p>

<p>The 28-year-old has been pursued by the Blues as manager Frank Lampard wants a new goalkeeper to usurp much-maligned Kepa Arrizabalaga as his No 1.</p>

<p>Talks with Mendy's club Rennes have been ongoing but according to his agent Djily Dieng a significant breakthrough has happened.</p>

<p>'The deal with Chelsea is almost done. Only the formalisation is remaining,' he told Extra Time on Thursday afternoon. </p>

<p>'It could be completed even on next hours'.</p>

<p>MORE TO FOLLOW </p>
